gurmukhi: nmo Awid ABMgy nmo Awid ABMgy ]5]95]
transliteration: Namo Aadh Abhane, Namo Aadh Abhane||5||95||
translation: Salutation to Him, Who is Primal and Immortal; Salutation to Him who is Primal and Immortal.5.95.

gurmukhi: ikqy kiRsn sy kIt kotY aupwey ]
transliteration: Kite Krisan Se Koot Kotai Oupaae||
translation: He hath Created millions of Krishnas like worms.
He Created them, annihilated them, again destroyed them, still again Created them.
He is Unfathomable, Fearless, Primal, Non-dual and Indestructible.
Yonder and Yonder is He, the supreme Lord, He is the Perfect Illuminator. 6.96.

gurmukhi: n AwDM n ibAwDM AgwDM srUpy ]
transliteration: Na Aadhan Na Biaadhan Agaddhan Daroope||
translation: He, the Unfathomable Entity is without the ailments of the mind and body.
He the Lord of Indivisible Glory and Master of eternal wealth from the very beginging.

gurmukhi: n jnmM n mrnM n brnM n ibAwDy ]
transliteration: Na Janamannd Na Maran Na Baranan Na Biaadhe||
translation: He is without birth, without death, without colour and without ailment.
He is Partless, Mighty, Unpunishable and Incorrigible.7.97.

gurmukhi: n nyhM n gyhM snyhM n swQy ]
transliteration: Na Nehan Na Gehan Sanehan Na Saathe||
translation: He is without love, without home, without affection and without company.

gurmukhi: n jwqy n pwqy n s`qRy n im`qRy ]
transliteration: Na Jaate Na Paate, Na Sattre Na Mittre||
translation: He is without caste, without line, without enemy and without friend.
That Imageless Lord was in the past, is in the present and will be in the future. 8.98.

gurmukhi: n rwXM n rMkM n rUpM n ryKM ]
transliteration: Na Raayan Na Rankan, Na Roopan Na Rekhan||
translation: He is neither the king, nor the poor, without form and without mark.
